Public Remarks: This can be your slice of northern Minnesota solitude! 81 acres of mixed-timber recreational land between Hibbing and Virginia in the heart of the Mesabi Iron Range. Whether you are looking for hunting, trail riding, or quiet enjoyment - this land offers the opportunity to just get away from it all. A rustic 16x24 Amish -built log cabin overlooking a swimmable 3-acre pond anchors the property, with two heated hunting stands on the northern corners. Deer, wildlife and small game frequent the property. Open construction cabin with an 8x16 loft for extra sleeping space. Antique propane gas stove and wood burning stove for heating and cooking. No electricity, but solar-charged batteries and a generator (not included) provide evening light. No running water on site. Outhouse near the cabin
